parameters.text:
=Write a personalized follow-up email to this lead:

Email: {{ $json["identity-profiles"][0].identities[0].value }}
Lead Status: {{ $json.properties.hs_lead_status.value }}
Notes Last Contacted (timestamp): {{ $json.properties.notes_last_contacted.value }}
Account Created Date (timestamp): {{ $json.properties.createdate.value }}

Context:
This lead was previously marked as "bad timing" and has not been contacted recently. 
The goal is to politely re-open the conversation and check if now is a better time to connect.

Write a short, natural follow-up email.

parameters.jsCode:
const rawOutput = $input.first().json.output || '';

let subject = 'Following up';
let body = 'Hi, just checking in to see if you had any questions. Let me know!';

try {
  const parsed = JSON.parse(rawOutput);
  if (parsed.subject) subject = parsed.subject;
  if (parsed.body) body = parsed.body;
} catch (e) {
  // fallback to defaults already set above
}

const leadData = $('Batch Leads (Split In Batches)').first().json;

return [{
  json: {
    subject,
    body,
    toEmail: leadData.properties.email,
    firstName: leadData.properties.firstname,
    lastName: leadData.properties.lastname,
    ownerId: leadData.properties.hubspot_owner_id
  }
}];

